<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12019j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12019j">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12019j"> 19(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ seahorses</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La derni&egrave;re invasion, celle des Normands, ne fut pas la moins terrible. Charlemagne s&apos;&eacute;tait d&eacute;j&agrave; inqui&eacute;t&eacute; de ces rois de mer, &ldquo;qui ne dormaient jamais sous les poutres enfum&eacute;es d&apos;un toit et ne vidaient jamais la corne de bi&egrave;re aupr&egrave;s d&apos;un foyer habit&eacute;&rdquo;. Il &eacute;tait devenu pensif &agrave; la vue de ces pirates du Nord, qui, sur de longs vaisseaux appel&eacute;s serpents de mer, rasaient les c&ocirc;tes et r&ocirc;daient aux embouchures des fleuves. Avec leurs proues &eacute;lanc&eacute;es, sculpt&eacute;es et peintes en t&ecirc;tes de dragon, avec leurs voiles rouges ray&eacute;es de noir, ces navires ressemblaient &agrave; des b&ecirc;tes fantastiques, &agrave; des monstres terriblement vivants. Admirablement construits, munis de rameurs excellents, &ldquo;ces chevaux de mer,&rdquo; &mdash; c&apos;est ainsi que les Norv&eacute;giens eux-m&ecirc;mes les nommaient, &mdash; montaient l&eacute;g&egrave;rement sur les plus grosses vagues et semblaient hennir de joie au fort de la temp&ecirc;te. <br><font color="green">[The last invasion, that of the Normans, was no less terrible. Charlemagne was already nervous about these kings of the sea, &ldquo;who never slept under the smoked beams of a roof and never emptied a horn of beer in a habitable hearth&rdquo;. He had become thoughtful at the sight of these pirates of the North, who, on long boats called sea serpents, raided the coasts and entered the river deltas. With their heightened prows, sculpted into the heads of dragons, with their red sails with black rays, these boats looked like fantastic beasts, monsters terribly alive. With admirable construction, with excellent rowers, &ldquo;these horses of the sea,&rdquo; &mdash; this is what the Norwegians called them,&mdash; rose lightly on the largest waves and seemed to neigh with joy at the height of the storm.]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 167</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
